bers of the apo research advisory group met for the first time including karen eggleston director of stanford's asia health policy program the apo has prepared two health systems in transition reports providing in depth profiles of the health systems of the philippines and fiji additional country health system profiles and policy briefs will be published in 2012 the research and analysis generated by the observatory is considered as a public good and is freely available at the apo website html+ read more asia pacific observatory of health systems and policies http www wpro who int asia_pacifi search ahpp news of interest working paper series on health and demographic change in the asia pacific december 15 2009 shorenstein aparc news does it matter how you pay doctors and hospitals evidence from the asia pacific july 16 2008 shorenstein aparc news announcing the asia pacific health policy forum march 10 2008 shorenstein aparc news conference on healthcare payment incentives in the asia pacific january 31 2008 shorenstein aparc announcement support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 725 2429 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
